Colombian Stocks: Coltejer, Ecopetrol, Pacific Rubiales Energy

-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 
2011-03-15T21:47:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/colombia-stock-movers-canacol-inversiones-argos-ecopetrol.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IGBC Index declined 2.4 percent to 13,942.09, while the
Colcap Index dropped 2.4 percent to 1,645.96.  Oil producers declined as crude prices fell to a two-week
low in New York on speculation that damage from  Japan ’s
earthquake may limit demand.    Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
tumbled 1.9 percent to 3,815 pesos.    Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)   plunged 5.5 percent
to 50,100 pesos, its lowest level since Oct. 4.    Coltejer SA (COLTEJ)  , the Medellin-based clothing maker
and exporter, jumped 3.6 percent to 86 centavos. U.S. Senator  Mitch McConnell  led 43 Republicans in vowing to block action on
President Barack Obama’s nominees for Commerce secretary and
other positions until Congress gets free-trade agreements with  South Korea , Colombia and Panama.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Camila Russo in New York at 
